<Topic>
  <Grid ControlType="RadioButton">
    <Row>
      <Header Span="6">New Hearing Loss</Header>
      <Button GroupName="1">
        <Header Span="2">No</Header>
        <Phrase Key="HearingLoss" />
        <Text Key="PhysicalExam.Neurological" Value="No new hearing loss." />
      </Button>
      <Button GroupName="1">
        <Header Span="2">Yes</Header>
        <Phrase Key="HearingLoss" />
        <Text Key="PhysicalExam.Neurological" Value="New hearing loss noted." />
      </Button>
      <Button GroupName="1">
        <Header Span="2">?</Header>
        <Phrase Key="HearingLoss" />
        <Text Key="PhysicalExam.Neurological" Value="Difficult to ascertain if there is a new hearing loss." />
      </Button>
    </Row>
    <Row>
      <Border Span="12">
        <TextBlock>A diagnosis of vestibular neuritis can be made if:
        1). Spontaneous or gaze evoked nystagmus are not bidirectional.
        2). No vertical skew deviation.
        3). Head Impulse testing is abnormal. (Abnormal if nystagmus.)
        4). No hearing loss. (Finger rub test.)</TextBlock>
      </Border>
    </Row>
  </Grid>
